.TH GAT-ARCHIVE 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-archive \- move a worktree to an archive directory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat archive
.I <ticket>
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Relocates a worktree (preserving it as a valid Git worktree) into an archive
root, by default
.IR ../<repo\-name>\-archive/ ,
using
.BR "git worktree move" .
Refuses to archive the primary worktree, and refuses a dirty worktree without
.BR \-\-force .
Validates that the archive destination is writable, and updates the usage
metadata to the new path.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-archive\-dir " path"
Archive root (default
.IR ../<repo>\-archive ).
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Archive a dirty worktree.
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Skip the confirmation prompt.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Show the planned archive move only.
.TP
.BI \-\-prefix " prefix" ", " \-\-no\-prefix
Ticket prefix handling.
.TP
.BI \-\-format " text|json"
Output format.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.EX
gat archive 12345
gat archive 12345 \-\-yes \-\-archive\-dir ~/archives
gat archive 12345 \-\-dry\-run
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-rm (1)
